label("$M$", M, S);
[/asy]

answer:
If $x = \angle BAC,$ then $\angle BDC = 3x.$  Since $AM = 11$ and $AD = 10,$ $DM = 1.$  Also, $\angle AMB = 90^\circ,$ so $\tan x = \frac{BM}{AM} = BM.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, M;

A = (0,11);
D = (0,1);
B = (-11/2,0);
C = (11/2,0);
M = (B + C)/2;

