label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, NW);
label("$M$", M, S);
[/asy]

Also, $\angle BDC = 3x$ and $BD = AM - AD = 11 - 10 = 1,$ so $\tan \angle BDC = 0.$  Since $\angle BDC = \angle BDM + \angle MDC = 3x,$
$$\tan \angle BDC = \tan 3x = \frac{3\tan x - \tan^3 x}{1 - 3\tan^2 x} = 0.$$For this to be true, the numerator must be 0, so $3\tan x - \tan^3 x = 0.$  Also, $\tan x \neq 0,$ so $\tan^2 x = 3.$  This means $\tan x = \sqrt{3},$ so $BM = \sqrt{3}$ and $AB = \sqrt{AM^2 + BM^2} = \sqrt{11^2 + (\sqrt{3})^2} = \sqrt{124} = 2\sqrt{31}.$  The perimeter of $\triangle ABC$ is $2AB + AC = 4\sqrt{31} + 2\sqrt{31} = \boxed{6\sqrt{31}}.$

